text: Saint-Laurent-du-Mont is a former commune. It is found in the Normandy region in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. In 2016, 189 people lived there. On 1 January 2019, it became a part of the commune Cambremer.Arrêté préfectoral 24 September 2018, p. 119 == References == Category:Former communes in Calvados
title: Saint-Laurent-du-Mont
